						               													<description>This is a game that needs no table. So you could play it on a train, in a plane or even in the back seat of the family car on a road trip.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players hold a hand of tiles as though playing cards, but have a score bag hanging on a loop from their wrist.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On a turn, a player will draw a random tile from a draw bag (the railway yard) that gets passed around after each turn. The draw bag holds rolling stock (locomotives and wagons) and loads.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Then the player discards a tile from their hand. That tile may go into their own score bag or back to the yard to get them an action.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;What players are trying to do with the score bag is create a loaded train, pulled by the correct locomotive type, worth the most points when the game ends.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
